sis on its structure, strategy, and argumentation, focusing especially on the tension between the actual practices of the anonymous client of the logographer and civic ideals invoked in the present case. The book is intended to be of interest to classicists, ancient historians and political theorists, but also to the general reader.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aLysias. 4aRedekunst. 4aRhetorik. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh  aLysias.  aoratory.  arhetoric.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2014z9783110369618oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG0 cEPUBz97831103911140 cprintz978311035433140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036226840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110362268423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110362268/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2014  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-GCNc2000d2014